{
  "texts": [
    "The limitations of the current approach were also evident in the handling of long-tail queries, where the model's performance was less consistent.",
    "The weighted RAG model handled long-tail queries with a 13.4% error rate, whereas the baseline model had an 18.7% error rate.",
    "Contextual irrelevance errors, where the generated output was not contextually appropriate, were reduced to 7.9% with the weighted RAG model, compared to 10.4% for the baseline.",
    "Superficial accuracy, where the responses appeared correct on the surface but were inaccurate upon closer examination, was observed at 9.3% for the weighted RAG model and 12.6% for the baseline.",
    "These findings highlighted the need for further refinement of the weighting mechanism and the incorporation of more sophisticated context-awareness strategies to mitigate these issues."
  ]
}